Python Installation Information:

    Python is installed using pyenv (https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv)
    
    To update pyenv:
        brew upgrade pyenv
    To list installed Python versions:
        pyversions
        or
        pyenv global
    To install a new Python version:
        pyinstall <version>
        or
        pyenv install <version>
    To switch Python versions:
        pyuse <py3_version> 2.7.18   # sets the default Python versions
        or
        pyenv shell <version>  # sets the Python version for the shell session
    For more pyenv usage:
        pyenv help
    For information on Python virtual environments:
        pipenv --help
        or
        pipenvstart --help   ## small wrapper to for pipenv
    
    To run as iPython:
        ipython <target>
        
    Share local directory as a HTTP server using Python:
        pyserver
    
    To dump currently installed pip packages to piprequirements.txt:
        pipdump
    To install pip packages from piprequirements.txt in the current directory
        pipreq
    
    Default Python package installations are found in the pip-file:
        ~/Workspace/__space__/.dotfiles/packages/pip
    Python installations are found in:
        ~/.pyenv/versions/
    
Global Pip Packages:

    numpy - Fundamental package for array computing with Python
    scipy - Fundamental algorithms for scientific computing in Python
    matplotlib - Python plotting package
    pandas - Powerful data structures for data analysis, time series, and statistics
    sympy - Computer algebra system (CAS) in Python
    seaborn - Statistical data visualization
    scikit-learn - A set of python modules for machine learning and data mining
    ipython - Productive Interactive Computing
    bokeh - Interactive plots and applications in the browser from Python
    Flask - A simple framework for building complex web applications
    sqlalchemy - Database Abstraction Library
    mysqlclient - Python interface to MySQL
    requests - Python HTTP for Humans
    beautifulsoup4 - Screen-scraping library
    urllib3 - HTTP library with thread-safe connection pooling, file post, and more
    pytest - simple powerful testing with Python
    pillow - Python Imaging Library (Fork)
    nltk - Natural Language Toolkit
    rshell - A remote shell for working with MicroPython boards
    adafruit-ampy - A command line tool to interact with a CircuitPython or MicroPython boards over a serial connection
